size /saɪz/

(sizing,sized,sizes) 

1. N-VAR The size of something is how big or small it is. Something's size is determined by comparing it to other things, counting it, or measuring it. 大小; 规模 

例： In 1970 the average size of a French farm was 19 hectares. 1970年法国农场的平均面积是19公顷。 

例： ...shelves containing books of various sizes. …摆放着大大小小书籍的书架。 

2. N-UNCOUNT The size of something is the fact that it is very large. 巨大; 庞大 

例： He knows the size of the task. 他知道任务很重。 

3. N-COUNT A size is one of a series of graded measurements, especially for things such as clothes or shoes. 尺寸; 尺码 

例： My sister is the same height but only a size 

12. 我妹妹的身高一样，但只穿12码的。 

4. V to sort according to size 按大小排列 

5. N a thin gelatinous mixture, made from glue, clay, or wax, that is used as a sealer or filler on paper, cloth, or plaster surfaces 胶料; 浆糊 (Also called sizing) 

6. V to treat or coat (a surface) with size 上浆; 上涂料

